Security operatives and civilians were reportedly killed in Zamfara on Monday during an attack on PGP company in Birnin Tudu, Bakura Local Government Area. The officers involved include two policemen and two Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC). They were identified as Yusuf Usama, Ibrahim Bello, Zaharadden Yushau, Sani Abubakar. The late civilians are Ahmed Murtala and Tanimu Muhammad (a driver). The victims were attacked in Gora village at a location called MS Team while the expatriates from China were working. The gunmen set the Hilux patrol vehicle used by the security personnel ablaze and carted away their arms. The police command has sent a team to the scene and commenced an investigation. Zamfara police repel banditsâ€™ attack, kill scores